      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "AJCC",
    "date_created": "2020-04-29T03:24:28Z",
    "date_modified": "2022-05-27T07:24:11Z",
    "description": "This item indicates the version of the AJCC API incorporated into the cancer registry software that created the record with TNM stage data in the 8^th^ and later versions. It should be recorded the first time the AJCC ID (including a value of 8) is determined. If the registry software incorporates the APCC API directly, the value is obtained from AJCC’s API. If the software instead incorporates AJCC’s Cancer Surveillance API, the value can be returned from there. \n\nA valid value is required for all cases diagnosed 2018 or later that have values entered in the AJCC or related data items. Cases abstracted prior to implementation of this data item will be assigned a value of 08.XX.XX during the conversion to v21.\n\n",
    "rationale": "Over time the definitions and other content contained in the AJCC’s API may change. This item identifies the original API content used to code the TNM data.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "Derived",
    "seer_collect": "Derived, when available",
    "cccr_collect": "Required, when available",
    "format": "Characters may be alphanumeric and include decimal points.",
    "code_note": "Blank is allowable in the case that no AJCC or related input items are coded. \n\n\n",
    "allowable_values": "Values of the form XX.YY.ZZ, Blank"
  },
  {
    "item_number": "2158",
    "item_name": "AJCC Cancer Surveillance DLL Version Current",
    "item_data_type": "text",
    "item_length": "13",
    "year_implemented": "2021",
    "version_implemented": "21",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "ajccCancerSurvApiVersionCurrent",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "AJCC",
    "date_created": "2020-04-29T15:25:30Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-05-11T20:42:26.80507Z",
    "description": "This item indicates the most recently accessed version of the Cancer Surveillance .dll incorporated into the cancer registry software that created the record with stage data diagnosed 2018 and later. AJCC Cancer Surveillance DLL Version Current \\[2158\\] will be assigned based on the version of the AJCC Cancer Surveillance .dll in use in the registry software system. It must be updated every time a new version is incorporated into your system and all relevant cases should be updated to reflect the same value.\r\n\r\n*   For cases diagnosed prior to 2018, this field should remain blank.\r\n*   For cases diagnosed in 2018-2020, this field should be set to the AJCC Cancer Surveillance .dll version in use at the time of implementation.\r\n*   For cases diagnosed in 2018 and later abstracted after implementation, use the AJCC Cancer Surveillance .dll version in use at the time the case is being abstracted.\r\n\r\nThe value is obtained from the .dll.  \r\n   \r\nFormerly: AJCC Cancer Surveillance API Version Current",
    "general_notes": "This data item will be generated by registry software.\r\n\r\nThe AJCC Cancer Surveillance API contains contents to support collection of AJCC''s TNM, EOD, SSDIs, and directly entered Summary Stage 2018. The underlying contents are loaded from AJCC''s API and SEER''s web service. The API is versioned independently from the imported contents.\r\n\r\nThe value indicates the version of the Cancer Surveillance API used most recently to code the items listed below and is obtained from the API. It should be recorded the first time the AJCC ID (including a value of XX) and/or Schema ID is determined and should be updated each time an updated AJCC Cancer Surveillance API is implemented.\r\n\r\nRelated Input Fields\r\n\r\n*   AJCC TNM Clin T (also Path and Post Therapy T) \\[1001, 1011, 1021\\]\r\n*   AJCC TNM Clin N (also Path and Post Therapy N) \\[1002, 1012, 1022\\]\r\n*   AJCC TNM Clin M (also Path and Post Therapy M) \\[1003, 1013, 1023\\]\r\n*   AJCC TNM Clin Stage Group (also Path and Post Therapy Stage Group \\[1004, 1014, 1024\\])\r\n*   Summary Stage 2018 \\[764\\]\r\n*   EOD Primary Tumor \\[772\\]\r\n*   EOD Regional Nodes \\[774\\]\r\n*   EOD Mets \\[776\\]\r\n*   All SSDIs (see SSDI manual for complete list).",
    "rationale": "Over time, the definitions and other content contained in the .dll may change. This item identifies the current .dll content used to code the items.",
    "npcr_collect": "Derived",
    "coc_collect": "Derived",
    "seer_collect": "No recommendation",
    "cccr_collect": "Required, when available",
    "alternate_names": [
      "AJCC Cancer Surveillance API Version Current"
    ],
    "format": "N[N].N[N].N[N].N[NNN] Four groups of one or more digits separated by periods. The first group identifies the underlying AJCC edition number. The second a major revision. The third a minor revision. The last group identifies the build. The value 08.01.05.0025 would represent the 8th edition, 1st major revision, 5th minor revision, and the 25th build of the API.",
    "allowable_values": "Numbers, decimal points"
  },
  {
    "item_number": "2159",
    "item_name": "AJCC Cancer Surveillance DLL Version Original",
    "item_data_type": "text",
    "item_length": "13",
    "year_implemented": "2021",
    "version_implemented": "21",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "ajccCancerSurvApiVersionOriginal",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "AJCC",
    "date_created": "2020-04-29T11:26:23Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-05-11T20:43:54.595775Z",
    "description": "This item indicates the version of the AJCC Cancer Surveillance .dll incorporated into the cancer registry software that created the record with stage data diagnosed 2018 and later. It should be recorded the first time the AJCC ID (including a value of XX) and/or Schema ID are determined using the .dll. The value is obtained from the .dll.\r\n\r\nFormerly: AJCC Cancer Surveillance API Version Original",
    "general_notes": "This data item will be generated by registry software.  \r\n   \r\nThe AJCC Cancer Surveillance API contains contents to support collection of AJCC’s TNM, EOD, and directly entered Summary Stage 2018. The underlying contents are loaded from AJCC’s API and SEER’s web service. The API is versioned independently from the imported contents.  \r\n   \r\nThe value indicates the version of the AJCC Cancer Surveillance API originally used to code the items listed below and is obtained from the API. It should be recorded the first time the AJCC ID (including a value of XX) and/or Schema ID is determined and should not be updated each time the related input fields are modified.  However, if changes made to the diagnosis and/or date of diagnosis result in a different AJCC ID and/or Schema ID, the value for AJCC Cancer Surveillance DLL Version Original should be reset.  \r\n \r\n\r\n  \r\n**Related Input Fields**\r\n\r\n*   AJCC TNM Clin T (also Path and Post Therapy T) \\[1001, 1011, 1021\\]\r\n*   AJCC TNM Clin N (also Path and Post Therapy N) \\[1002, 1012, 1022\\]\r\n*   AJCC TNM Clin M (also Path and Post Therapy M) \\[1003, 1013, 1023\\]\r\n*   AJCC TNM Clin Stage Group (also Path and Post Therapy Stage Group \\[1004, 1014, 1024\\])\r\n*   Summary Stage 2018 \\[764\\]\r\n*   EOD Primary Tumor \\[772\\]\r\n*   EOD Regional Nodes \\[774\\]\r\n*   EOD Mets \\[776\\]\r\n*   All SSDIs (see SSDI manual for complete list).",
    "rationale": "Over time, the definitions and other content contained in the .dll may change. This item identifies the original content used to code the items.",
    "npcr_collect": "Derived",
    "coc_collect": "Derived",
    "seer_collect": "No recommendation",
    "cccr_collect": "Required, when available",
    "format": "N[N].N[N].N[N].N[NNN] Four groups of one or more digits separated by periods. The first group identifies the underlying AJCC edition number. The second a major revision. The third a minor revision. The last group identifies the build. The value 08.01.05.0025 would represent the 8th edition, 1st major revision, 5th minor revision, and the 25th build of the API.",
    "allowable_values": "Numbers, decimal points"
  },
