    "description": "Code for the behavior of the tumor being reported using ICD-O-3. NAACCR adopted ICD-O-3 as the standard coding system for tumors diagnosed beginning January 1, 2001, and later recommended that prior cases be converted from ICD-O-2. See Behavior (92-00) ICD-O-2 \\[430\\], for ICD-O-2 codes.\r\n\r\nJuvenile astrocytoma is coded as borderline in ICD-O-3; North American registries report as 9421/3.",
    "clarification": "**Clarification of Required Status**\r\n\r\nBehavior is required by all standard-setting organizations for tumors diagnosed on or after January 1, 2001, and recommended (by conversion from ICD-O-2 codes) for tumors diagnosed before 2001.\r\n\r\nWhen the histologic type is coded according to the ICD-O-3, the histology code must be reported in Histologic Type ICD-O-3 \\[522\\], with behavior coded in Behavior Code ICD-O-3 \\[523\\].\r\n\r\nFor information on required status for related data items for histologic type and behavior when coded according to ICD-O-2, see Histology (92-00) ICD-O-2 \\[420\\] and Behavior (92-00) ICD-O-2 \\[430\\].",
    "npcr_collect": "Required",
    "coc_collect": "Required",
    "seer_collect": "Required",
    "cccr_collect": "Required",
    "alternate_names": [
      "Behavior Code (CoC)",
      "ICD-O-3 Behaviour (CCCR)"
    ],
    "code_note": "Valid codes are 0-3. See ICD-O-3,^14^ page 66, for behavior codes and definitions.",
    "allowable_values": "0-3, Refer to ICD-O-3"
  },
