    ],
    "section": "Demographic",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2016-10-19T18:59:49Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-11-30T12:28:57.466407Z",
    "description": "Code indicating basis of assignment of census tract for an individual record. Helpful in identifying cases geocoded from incomplete information or P.O. Box. This item is not coded by the hospital. Central registry staff assign the code based on the results of geocoding.",
    "npcr_collect": "Derived",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Derived",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "code_note": "**Clarification of NPCR Required Status**\r\n\r\n| Census-1990 data items: | Census-2000 data items: | Census-2010 data items: | Census-2020 data items: |\r\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\r\n| Census Tract 1970/80/90 \\[110\\] | Census Tract 2000 \\[130\\] | Census Tract 2010 \\[135\\] | Census Tract 2020  \\[371\\] |\r\n| Census Tr Cert 1970/80/90 \\[364\\] | Census Tr Certainty 2000 \\[365\\] | Census Tr Certainty 2010 \\[367\\] | Census Tr Certainty 2020 \\[369\\] |\r\n| Census Tract Cod Sys--1970/80/90 \\[120\\] |   |   |   |\r\n\r\nInformation on census tract and census tract certainty is required. Census Tract and Census Tract Certainty should be recorded in the year-appropriate data item fields in order to reflect demographic information at the time of diagnosis. Until the 2020 Census is completed and data are available for geocoding, tumors diagnosed in 2020 or later, should be coded to the 2010 census definitions and recorded in Census Tract 2010 \\[135\\] and Census Tr Certainty 2000 \\[367\\]. When the 2020 Census data are available for geocoding, tumors diagnosed in 2020 or later must be coded to the 2020 census tract definitions and recorded in Census Tract 2020 \\[371\\] and Census Tract Certainty 2020 \\[369\\]. For tumors diagnosed between January 1, 2018, and December 31, 2019, use of Census Tract 2020 \\[371\\] and Census Track Certainty 2020 \\[369\\] is recommended.",
    "allowable_values": "1-6, 9, Blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Census tract based on complete and valid street address of residence"
      },
      {
        "code": "2",
        "description": "Census tract based on residence ZIP + 4"
      },
      {
        "code": "3",
        "description": "Census tract based on residence ZIP + 2"
      },
      {
        "code": "4",
        "description": "Census tract based on residence ZIP code only"
      },
      {
        "code": "5",
        "description": "Census tract based on ZIP code of P.O. Box"
      },
      {
        "code": "6",
        "description": "Census tract/BNA based on residence city where city has only one census tract, or based on residence ZIP code where ZIP code has only one census tract"
      },
      {
        "code": "9",
        "description": "Not assigned, geocoding attempted"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not assigned, geocoding not attempted"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1189",
    "item_name": "Chromosome 16q: Loss of Heterozygosity",
    "item_data_type": "numeric",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2025",
    "version_implemented": "25",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "chromosome16qLossHeterozygosity",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Stage/Prognostic Factors",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR/SEER",
    "date_created": "2024-04-26T17:44:25.117582Z",
    "date_modified": "2025-05-15T01:27:05.670148Z",
    "description": "Chromosome 16q: Loss of Heterozygosity (LOH) refers to the loss of genetic material normally found on the short arm of one of the patient''s two copies of chromosome 16. Occurs in approximately 5% of favorable (non-anaplastic) histology Wilm’s tumor (FHWT) cells and has been shown to be associated with inferior relapse-free survival (RFS) and overall survival (OS) in patients with FH Wilm’s tumor. This testing is commonly done in conjunction with Chromosome 1p: Loss of Heterozygosity (NAACCR ID: 3801) and Chromosome 1q: Gain of heterozygosity (GOH). (NAACCR ID: 1190: Chromosome 1q Status).\r\n\r\nThis is a special molecular diagnostic test performed on tumor tissue to identify loss of genetic material found on the long arm of one of the patient’s two copies of chromosome 16. A normal cell will contain two complete copies of each chromosome, one from each parent, and this normal state is termed heterozygous. Loss of heterozygosity (LOH) is an abnormal state reflecting loss of the whole arm of chromosome 16q following a chromosomal translocation event.",
    "general_notes": "**Source documents:** molecular pathology report (may be addendum to original pathology report).",
    "rationale": "This is part of the National Childhood Cancer Registry (NCCR) project to collect more specific information on pediatric patients. Registries part of the NCCR will start collection on specific pediatric data items with 2024+ diagnoses.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Required, site specific; when available",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "code_note": "**Note 1: Effective years**\r\n\r\n*   This SSDI is effective for diagnosis years 2024+\r\n*   For cases diagnosed 2018-2023, this SSDI must be blank\r\n\r\n**Note 2:** **Physician statement**\r\n\r\n*   Physician statement of Chromosome 16q deletion/LOH can be used to code this data item when no other information is available.",
    "allowable_values": "0, 1, 7, 8,9",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "0",
        "description": "Chromosome 16q deletion/LOH not identified/not present/negative"
      },
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Chromosome 16q deletion/LOH present/positive"
      },
      {
        "code": "7",
        "description": "Test ordered, results not in chart"
      },
      {
        "code": "8",
        "description": "Not applicable:  Information not collected for this case  \r\n(If this item is required by your standard setter, use of code 8 will result in an edit error.)"
      },
      {
        "code": "9",
        "description": "Not documented in medical record\r\n\r\nCannot be determined by pathologist\r\n\r\nChromosome 16q: LOH not assessed or unknown if assessed"
      }
    ]
  },
