    "source_of_standard": "NPCR",
    "date_created": "2011-11-09T14:47:21Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-09-15T07:07:41.058041Z",
    "description": "Date the abstract (or source record) is received by the central cancer registry for the respective tumor. If multiple reports are received from two or more sources and if a single date is needed, use the date the first abstract (or source record) was received from any source. See Chapter [**Data Descriptor Table**](https://apps.naaccr.org/data-dictionary/data-dictionary/version=24/chapter-view/data-descriptor-table/) for date format.",
    "rationale": "This item is used to assess and monitor the timeliness of reporting. Timeliness of abstracting (and reporting) is a concern for all standard-setting organizations. This item can be used with the Date of 1st Contact \\[580\\] or the Path--Date of Specimen Collection \\[7320\\] to measure timeliness of reporting to central cancer registries by individual reporting facilities. This data item also can be used with the Date Tumor Record Availbl \\[2113\\] to measure timeliness of processing within the central cancer registry.",
