    "date_modified": "2022-05-27T07:24:11Z",
    "description": "USPS abbreviation for the state (including U.S. territories, commonwealths, or possessions), or Canada Post abbreviation for the Canadian province/territory of the follow-up contact’s current usual residence. If the patient has multiple tumors, the follow-up contact state should be the same for all tumors. Effective with NAACCR Volume II, Version 13, a new data item, FollowUp Contact--Country [1847] was added to the standard transmission record layout. The UDS Committee expects the new item to supplement the use of Follow-Up Contact--State [1844].",
    "rationale": "Sometimes registries carry out follow-up by contacting the patient and other contacts by a letter or phone call to ascertain their vital status. When a patient''s current address is unknown or the patient is for some reason not to be contacted (e.g., patient is a minor child), the most current name, address and phone number of another contact, such as a relative or neighbor are needed. This information may also be useful for conducting research studies.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "No recommendation",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "format": "Upper case",
    "code_description": "In addition to USPS and Canadian Postal Service abbreviations",
