    "description": "Country code for the address of follow-up contact’s current usual residence. If the patient has multiple tumors, the country of follow-up contact residence should be the same for all tumors. This data item became part of the NAACCR transmission record effective with Volume II, Version 13 in order to include country and state for each geographic item and to use interoperable codes. It supplements the item FOLLOW UP CONTACT--STATE [1844].",
