  {
    "item_number": "1193",
    "item_name": "FOXO1 Gene Rearrangements",
    "item_data_type": "numeric",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2025",
    "version_implemented": "25",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "foxo1GeneRearrangements",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Stage/Prognostic Factors",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR/SEER",
    "date_created": "2024-04-26T13:50:56.751163Z",
    "date_modified": "2025-05-15T00:39:44.42316Z",
    "description": "FOXO1 gene rearrangement fusions are found to be positive in about 85% of alveolar rhabdomyosarcoma patients, while they are generally negative for embryonal rhabdomyosarcomas. The presence of these fusions indicates a poor prognosis. Identifying these fusions will also provide new therapeutic opportunities for the treatment of fusion positive rhabdomyosarcomas (FP-RMS).",
    "general_notes": "**Source documents:** molecular pathology report (may be addendum to original pathology report)",
    "rationale": "This is part of the National Childhood Cancer Registry (NCCR) project to collect more specific information on pediatric patients, specifically for Rhabdomyosarcoma. Registries part of the NCCR will start collection on specific pediatric data items with 2024+ diagnoses.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Required, site specific; when available",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "alternate_names": [
      "FKHR-PAX3",
      "FKHR-PAX7"
    ],
    "code_note": "**Note 1: Effective years**\r\n\r\n*   This SSDI is effective for diagnosis years 2024+\r\n*   For cases diagnosed 2018-2023, this SSDI must be blank\r\n\r\n**Note 2:** **Physician statement**\r\n\r\n*   Physician statement of FOXO1 gene rearrangements can be used to code this data item when no other information is available.\r\n\r\n**Note 3: Applicable histologies**\r\n\r\n*   FOXO1 may be recorded all sarcomas; however, it is primary done for Alveolar Rhabdomyosarcomas\r\n*   Embryonal Rhabdomyosarcomas are usually negative, and therefore the test is usually not done. \r\n*   Code 9 if information is not available",
    "allowable_values": "0-4, 7-9",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "0",
        "description": "No gene rearrangements (fusions) identified"
      },
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "FOXO1-PAX3 gene rearrangement (fusion) present"
      },
      {
        "code": "2",
        "description": "FOXO1-PAX7 gene rearrangement (fusion) present"
      },
      {
        "code": "3",
        "description": "FOXO1-PAX3 and FOXO1-PAX7 gene rearrangements (fusions) present"
      },
      {
        "code": "4",
        "description": "FOXO1 gene rearrangement present, fusion partner not known"
      },
      {
        "code": "7",
        "description": "Test ordered, results not in chart"
      },
      {
        "code": "8",
        "description": "Not applicable: Information not collected for this case  \r\n(If this information is required by your standard setter, use of code 8 may result in an edit error.)"
      },
      {
        "code": "9",
        "description": "Not documented in medical record\r\n\r\nCannot be determined by pathologist\r\n\r\nFOXO1 gene rearrangement not assessed or unknown if assessed"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "86",
    "item_name": "Geocoding Quality Code",
    "item_data_type": "alpha",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2024",
    "version_implemented": "24",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "geocodingQualityCode",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Demographic",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2023-06-22T00:59:08.757044Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-07-11T02:29:09.262488Z",
    "description": "Spatial analysis of cancer data often requires identifying case records that were geocoded. Researchers and registry staff can use this code to select geocoded records and determine which records need to be reviewed and geocoded again. \r\n\r\nHistorically, Census Tract Certainty \\[369\\] and NAACCR GIS Coordinate Quality \\[366\\] codes have been used to determine which geocoded cases require manual review. However, this code represents an improvement over these variables and is based on the geocoded data''s precision and accuracy. \r\n\r\nCode describing the quality of the geocoding match. The code indicates whether an address run through the NAACCR geocoder matched, failed to match, or needs to be reviewed. \r\n\r\nThis measure is referred to as Micro Match Status in the NAACCR geocoder documentation and has been in use since July 2017.",
    "general_notes": "**Application:**\r\n\r\n*   Cases in the “M” or “I” categories are considered high quality matches for state, county, or sub-county (small area) uses. \r\n*   Cases in the “R” category require manual review prior to using the data for geospatial analysis below county (small area), but can be used for county-based uses. These “Review” cases should be run through the NAACCR Geocoder as a separate batch run using “Exhaustive Search.” NAACCR has made an interface available, MI GeoCorrect Tool, to assist users in manually selecting among multiple potential addresses (or label as “Fail”). \r\n*   Cases in the “F” or “Fail” category geocoding will need to be reviewed, possibly corrected, and geocoded again before use.",
    "npcr_collect": "Derived, when available",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Derived",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "code_note": "This variable is not coded directly. The code is directly output by the NAACCR/AGGIE Geocoder or MI GeoCorrect Tool.",
    "allowable_values": "M,I,R,F",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "M",
        "description": "**Match**. Geocoding was competed and the address matched"
      },
      {
        "code": "I",
        "description": "**Interactive.** Geocoding was completed and the address matched after manual review in MI GeoCorrect Tool."
      },
      {
        "code": "R",
        "description": "**Review**. Geocoding was completed and the address needs to be manually reviewed before using below county-level."
      },
      {
        "code": "F",
        "description": "**Fail/non-match.** Geocoding was completed and the address needs to manually reviewed and modified and geocoded again."
