  {
    "item_number": "1187",
    "item_name": "Intl Neuroblastoma Path Prog Class (INPC)",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2025",
    "version_implemented": "25",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "inpc",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Stage/Prognostic Factors",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR/SEER",
    "date_created": "2024-04-27T01:42:46.579455Z",
    "date_modified": "2024-05-30T20:55:27.196601Z",
    "description": "The International Neuroblastoma Pathology Prognostic Classification (INPC) categorizes neuroblastomas as favorable or unfavorable histologies based on the following factors: age, neuroblastic maturation, Schwannian stromal content, Mitosis-kayorrhexis index (MKI), and degree of differentiation (grade). \r\n\r\nThe International Neuroblastoma Pathology Prognostic Classification (INPC) (unfavorable versus favorable histology) is a biologically relevant classification based on morphologic features of neuroblastic tumors which has prognostic indications. It is based on the following criteria\r\n\r\n*   Age\r\n*   Neuroblastic maturation\r\n*   Schwannian stromal content\r\n*   Mitosis-kayorrhexis index (MKI)\r\n*   Degree of differentiation (grade)",
    "general_notes": "**Source documents:** pathology report",
    "rationale": "This is part of the National Childhood Cancer Registry (NCCR) project to collect more specific information on pediatric patients. Registries part of the NCCR will start collection on specific pediatric data items with 2024+ diagnoses.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Required, site specific; when available",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "alternate_names": [
      "International Neuroblastoma Pathology Prognostic Classification (INPC)",
      "Shimada Classification",
      "Unfavorable histology, or Favorable histology"
    ],
    "code_note": "**Note 1: Effective years**\r\n\r\n*   This SSDI is effective for diagnosis years 2024+\r\n*   For cases diagnosed 2018-2023, this SSDI must be blank\r\n\r\n**Note 2: Physician statement**\r\n\r\n*   Physician statement of unfavorable vs favorable histology can be used to code this data item when no other information is available, provided there is information that the results are from a biopsy or surgical resection without neoadjuvant therapy.\r\n\r\n**Note 3: Neoadjuvant Therapy**\r\n\r\n*   The INPC results are to be coded based on either biopsy or surgical resection (without neoadjuvant therapy).\r\n*   **Code 9** if the only results are from a post neoadjuvant surgical resection.",
    "code_description": "For further information, refer to the **Neuroblastoma** cancer protocol published by the College of American Pathologists",
    "allowable_values": "0, 1, 7, 8, 9",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "0",
        "description": "Unfavorable"
      },
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Favorable"
      },
      {
        "code": "7",
        "description": "Test ordered, results not in chart"
      },
      {
        "code": "8",
