    "description": "Ki-67 (MIB-1) (Proliferative Index) is a marker of cell proliferation. A high value indicates a tumor that is proliferating more rapidly. Codes and coding instructions for this data item are site-specific.",
    "rationale": "Ki-67 (MIB-1) (Proliferative Index) is a Registry Data Collection Variable in AJCC. It was a new data item for breast cases diagnosed 1/1/2018+. It will apply to neuroendocrine tumors (NET) of the gastrointestinal tract (AJCC Chapters 29 – 34) for cases diagnosed 1/1/2021+. High Ki-67 is an adverse prognostic factor and Ki-67 is a component of grade for these tumors. NCCN guidelines recommend that tumor differentiation, mitotic rate and Ki-67 should be recorded in the pathology report for these tumors.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "Required, site specific",
    "seer_collect": "Collected by SEER from CoC-accredited hospitals",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "code_note": "Each Site-Specific Data Item (SSDI) applies only to selected primary sites, histologies, and years of diagnosis. Depending on applicability and standard-setter requirements, SSDIs may be left blank.",
    "allowable_values": "0.0-100.0, XXX.4, XXX.5, XXX.6, XXX.7, XXX.8, XXX.9",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "0.0-100.0",
        "description": "0.0 to 100.0 percent positive: enter percent positive"
      },
      {
        "code": "XXX.4",
        "description": "Ki-67 stated as less than 3%"
      },
      {
        "code": "XXX.5",
        "description": "Ki-67 stated as 3%-20%"
      },
      {
        "code": "XXX.6",
        "description": "Ki-67 stated as greater than 20%"
      },
      {
        "code": "XXX.7",
        "description": "Test done, actual percentage not stated"
      },
      {
        "code": "XXX.8",
