  {
    "item_number": "1985",
    "item_name": "Over-ride Acsn/Class/Seq",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2001",
    "version_implemented": "9",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "overRideAcsnClassSeq",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2011-11-10T00:47:21Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-09-15T09:12:47.548664Z",
    "description": "Some computer edits identify errors. Others indicate possible errors that require manual review for resolution. To eliminate the need to review the same cases repeatedly, over-ride flags have been developed to indicate that data in a record (or records) have been reviewed and, while unusual, are correct.\r\n\r\nThis over-ride is used with the following edit in the NAACCR Metafile of the EDITS software: Accession Number, Class of Case, Seq Number (CoC).",
    "rationale": "Some edits check for code combinations that are possible, but quite rare. If the code combination generates an error message and review of the case indicates that the codes are correct for the case, then the over-ride flag is used to skip the edit in the future. See [**Standards for Cancer Registries, Standard Data Edits**](https://www.naaccr.org/standard-data-edits/).\r\n\r\n**Over-ride Flag as Used in the EDITS Software Package**\r\n\r\nThe edit, Accession Number, Class of Case, Seq Number (CoC), checks the following:\r\n\r\n1.  If the case is the only case or the first of multiple cases diagnosed at the facility (Sequence Number--Hospital = 00, 01, 60, or 61, and Class of Case = 00, 10-14, or 40), then the first 4 characters of the Accession Number--Hosp must equal the year of the Date of 1st Contact.\r\n2.  If the case is first diagnosed at autopsy (Class of Case = 38) and the case is the only case or the first of multiple cases for a patient (Sequence Number--Hospital = 00, 01, 60, or 61), then the first 4 characters of the Accession Number--Hosp must equal the year of the Date of Last Contact AND must equal the year of the Date of 1st Contact.\r\n3.  If the case is first diagnosed at autopsy (Class of Case = 38) and the case is not the first case for a patient (Sequence Number--Hospital) greater than 01 or greater than 61), then the year of the Date of 1st Contact must equal the year of Date of Last Contact.\r\n\r\nThere are some exceptions to the above rules. Over-ride Acsn/Class/Seq may be used to override the edit when the circumstances fit the following situation or one similar to it:\r\n\r\nThe case may be the only or the first of multiple malignant cases for a patient (Sequence Number--Hospital = 00 or 01), but there is an earlier benign case (with an earlier year of the Date of 1st Contact) to which the Accession Number--Hosp applies.\r\n\r\n**Instructions for Coding**\r\n\r\n1.  If edit generates an error or warning message, verify that the Accession Number--Hosp, Sequence Number--Hospital, and Class of Case are correct.\r\n2.  Leave blank if the program does not generate an error message for the edit Accession Number, Class of Case, Seq Number (CoC).\r\n3.  Leave blank and correct any errors for the case if an item is discovered to be incorrect.\r\n4.  Code 1 if review of accession number, sequence number and class of case verifies that they have been coded correctly and there is an unusual combination of these data items.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "No recommendation",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "alternate_names": [
      "Over-ride Accession/Class of Case/Sequence"
    ],
    "allowable_values": "1 or blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not reviewed or reviewed and corrected"
      },
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed as reported"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1990",
    "item_name": "Over-ride Age/Site/Morph",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "overRideAgeSiteMorph",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "SEER",
    "date_created": "2011-11-09T19:47:21Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-09-15T09:17:29.296836Z",
    "description": "Some computer edits identify errors. Others indicate possible errors that require manual review for resolution. To eliminate the need to review the same cases repeatedly, over-ride flags have been developed to indicate that data in a record (or records) have been reviewed and, while unusual, are correct.\r\n\r\nThis over-ride is used with the following edits in the NAACCR Metafile of the EDITS software:\r\n\r\n*   Age, Primary Site, Morphology ICDO2 (SEER IF15)\r\n*   Age, Primary Site, Morphology ICDO3 (SEER IF15)\r\n*   Age, Primary Site, Morph ICDO3--Adult (SEER)\r\n*   Age, Primary Site, Morph ICDO3--Pediatric (NPCR)",
    "rationale": "Some edits check for code combinations that are possible, but quite rare. If the code combination generates an error message and review of the case indicates that the codes are correct for the case, then the over-ride flag is used to skip the edit in the future. See [**Standards for Cancer Registries, Standard Data Edits**](https://www.naaccr.org/standard-data-edits/).\r\n\r\n**Over-ride Flag as Used in the EDITS Software Package**\r\n\r\nSome cancers occur almost exclusively in certain age groups.\r\n\r\nEdits of the type Age, Primary Site, Morphology require review if a site/morphology combination occurs in an age group for which it is extremely rare. The edit Age, Primary Site, Morph ICDO3--Adult (SEER) edits cases with an Age at Diagnosis of 15 and older. The edit Age, Primary Site, Morph ICDO3--Pediatric (NPCR) edits cases with an Age at Diagnosis of less than 15. The edits Age, Primary Site, Morphology ICDO2 (SEER IF15) and Age, Primary Site, Morphology ICDO3 (SEER IF15) contain logic for all ages. \r\n\r\n**Instructions for Coding**\r\n\r\n1.  Leave blank if the program does not generate an error message (and if the case was not diagnosed _in utero_) for the edits of the type Age, Primary Site, Morphology.\r\n2.  Correct any errors for the case if an item is discovered to be incorrect.\r\n3.  Code 1 or 3 as indicated if review of items in the error or warning message confirms that all are correct.",
    "npcr_collect": "Required",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Required",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "alternate_names": [
      "Age/Site/Histology Interfield Review (Interfield Edit 15) (SEER #3)"
    ],
    "allowable_values": "1-3 or blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed that age/site/histology combination is correct as reported"
      },
      {
        "code": "2",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed that case was diagnosed *in utero*"
      },
      {
        "code": "3",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed that conditions 1 and 2 both apply"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not reviewed or reviewed and corrected."
      }
    ]
  },
