  {
    "item_number": "2040",
    "item_name": "Over-ride Histology",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "overRideHistology",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "SEER",
    "date_created": "2011-11-10T05:47:21Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-09-15T09:22:32.160863Z",
    "description": "Some computer edits identify errors. Others indicate possible errors that require manual review for resolution. To eliminate the need to review the same cases repeatedly, over-ride flags have been developed to indicate that data in a record (or records) have been reviewed and, while unusual, are correct.\r\n\r\nThis over-ride is used with the following edits in the NAACCR Metafile of the EDITS software:\r\n\r\n*   Diagnostic Confirmation, Behavior ICDO2 (SEER IF31)\r\n*   Diagnostic Confirmation, Behavior ICDO3 (SEER IF31)\r\n*   Morph (1973-91) ICD-O-1 (SEER MORPH)\r\n*   Morphology--Type/Behavior ICDO2 (SEER MORPH)\r\n*   Morphology--Type/Behavior ICDO3 (SEER MORPH)",
    "rationale": "Some edits check for code combinations that are possible, but quite rare. If the code combination generates an error message and review of the case indicates that the codes are correct for the case, then the over-ride flag is used to skip the edit in the future. See [**Standards for Cancer Registries, Standard Data Edits**](https://www.naaccr.org/standard-data-edits/). \r\n\r\n**Over-ride Flags as Used in the EDITS Software Package**\r\n\r\nEdits of the type Diagnostic Confirmation, Behavior differ in the use of ICD-O-2 or ICD-O-3 and check that, for _in situ_ cases (Behavior = 2), Diagnostic Confirmation specifies microscopic confirmation (1, 2, or 4).\r\n\r\nThe distinction between _in situ_ and invasive is very important to a registry, since prognosis is so different. Since the determination that a neoplasm has not invaded surrounding tissues, i.e., _in situ_, is made microscopically, cases coded _in situ_ in behavior should have a microscopic confirmation code. However, very rarely, a physician will designate a case noninvasive or _in situ_ without microscopic evidence.\r\n\r\nIf an edit of the type, Diagnostic Confirmation, Behavior, gives an error message or warning, check that Behavior and Diagnostic Confirmation have been coded correctly. Check carefully for any cytologic or histologic evidence that may have been missed in coding.\r\n\r\nEdits of the type, Morphology--Type/Behavior, perform the following check:\r\n\r\n1.  Codes listed in ICD-O-2 or ICD-O-3 with behavior codes of only 0 or 1 are considered valid, since the behavior matrix of ICD-O-2 and ICD-O-3 allows for the elevation of the behavior of such histologies when the tumor is _in situ_ or malignant. This edit forces review of these rare cases to verify that they are indeed _in situ_ or malignant.\r\n2.  The following histologies are generally not accepted as _in situ_: ICD-O-2 histologies 8000-8004, 8020, 8021, 8331, 8332, 8800-9054, 9062, 9082, 9083, 9110-9491, 9501-9989, ICD-O-3 histologies 8000-8005, 8020, 8021, 8331, 8332, 8800-9055, 9062, 9082, 9083, 9110-9493, 9501-9989. This edit forces review of these cases.\r\n3.  If a Morphology-Type/Behavior edit produces an error or warning message and the case is one in which the 4-digit morphology code is one that appears in ICD-O-2 or ICD-O-3 only with behavior codes of 0 or 1, or the case is one in which the 4-digit morphology code is not generally accepted with a behavior code of 2, verify the coding of morphology and that the behavior should be coded malignant or _in situ_. The registrar may need to consult a pathologist or medical advisor in problem cases.\r\n    *   Exceptions:\r\n    *   If year of Date of Diagnosis > 2000, then a behavior code of 1 is valid for the following ICD-O-2 histologies and no over-ride flag is needed: 8931, 9393, 9538, 9950, 9960-9962, 9980-9984, and 9989. Similarly, the following ICD-O-3 histologies are valid with a behavior code of 1: 8442, 8451, 8462, 8472, and 8473. If year of Date of Diagnosis > 2003, the following ICD-O-3 benign histologies will pass without review: 8146, 8271, 8861, 8897, 9121, 9122, 9131, 9161, 9350, 9351, 9352, 9360, 9361, 9383, 9384, 9394, 9412, 9413, 9444, 9492, 9493, 9506, 9531, 9532, 9533, 9534, 9537, 9541, 9550, 9562, and 9570.\r\n4.  Grade 5-8 with histologies not in the range of 9590-9948 is impossible.\r\n5.  Some terms in ICD-O-2 and ICD-O-3 carry an implied statement of grade. These histologies must be reported with the correct grade as stated below. An error of this type cannot be over-ridden.\r\n\r\n**ICD-O-2**  \r\n\\* 8020/34 Carcinoma, undifferentiated  \r\n\\* 8021/34 Carcinoma, anaplastic  \r\n\\* 8331/31 Follicular adenocarcinoma, well differentiated  \r\n\\* 8851/31 Liposarcoma, well differentiated  \r\n\\* 9062/34 Seminoma, anaplastic  \r\n\\* 9082/34 Malignant teratoma, undifferentiated  \r\n\\* 9083/32 Malignant teratoma, intermediate type  \r\n\\* 9401/34 Astrocytoma, anaplastic  \r\n\\* 9451/34 Oligodendroglioma, anaplastic  \r\n\\* 9511/31 Retinoblastoma, differentiated  \r\n\\* 9512/34 Retinoblastoma, undifferentiated  \r\n**ICD-O-3**  \r\n\\* 8020/34 Carcinoma, undifferentiated  \r\n\\* 8021/34 Carcinoma, anaplastic  \r\n\\* 8331/31 Follicular adenocarcinoma, well differentiated  \r\n\\* 9082/34 Malignant teratoma, undifferentiated  \r\n\\* 9083/32 Malignant teratoma, intermediate type  \r\n\\* 9401/34 Astrocytoma, anaplastic  \r\n\\* 9451/34 Oligodendroglioma, anaplastic  \r\n\\* 9511/31 Retinoblastoma, differentiated  \r\n\\* 9512/34 Retinoblastoma, undifferentiated\r\n\r\n**Instructions for Coding**\r\n\r\n1.  Leave blank if the program does not generate an error message for the edits of the types, Diagnostic Confirmation, Behav Code or Morphology--Type/Behavior.\r\n2.  Leave blank and correct any errors for the case if an item is discovered to be incorrect.\r\n3.  Code 1, 2, or 3 as indicated if review of all items in the error or warning message confirms that all are correct.",
    "npcr_collect": "Required",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Required",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "alternate_names": [
      "Histology/Behavior Interfield Review (Field Item Edit Morph)"
    ],
    "allowable_values": "1-3 or blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed that the pathologist states the primary to be \"*in situ*\" or \"malignant\" although the behavior code of the histology is designated as \"benign\" or \"uncertain\" in ICD-O-2 or ICD-O-3"
      },
      {
        "code": "2",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed that the behavior code is \"*in situ,*\" but the case is not microscopically confirmed"
      },
      {
        "code": "3",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed that conditions 1 and 2 both apply"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not reviewed or reviewed and corrected"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1986",
    "item_name": "Over-ride HospSeq/DxConf",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2001",
    "version_implemented": "9",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "overRideHospseqDxconf",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2011-11-10T05:47:21Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-09-15T09:13:52.410675Z",
    "description": "Some computer edits identify errors. Others indicate possible errors that require manual review for resolution. To eliminate the need to review the same cases repeatedly, over-ride flags have been developed to indicate that data in a record (or records) have been reviewed and, while unusual, are correct.\r\n\r\nThis over-ride is used with the following edit in the NAACCR Metafile of the EDITS software:\r\n\r\n*   Diagnostic Confirm, Seq Num--Hosp (CoC)",
    "rationale": "Some edits check for code combinations that are possible, but quite rare. If the code combination generates an error message and review of the case indicates that the codes are correct for the case, then the over-ride flag is used to skip the edit in the future. See [**Standards for Cancer Registries, Standard Data Edits**](https://www.naaccr.org/standard-data-edits/). \r\n\r\n**Over-ride Flag as Used in the EDITS Software Package**\r\n\r\nThe edit, Diagnostic Confirm, Seq Num--Hosp (CoC), does the following:\r\n\r\n1.  If any case is one of multiple primaries and is not microscopically confirmed or lacks a positive lab test/marker study, i.e., Diagnostic Confirmation > 5 and Sequence Number--Hospital > 00 (more than one primary), review is required.\r\n2.  If Primary Site specifies an ill-defined or unknown primary (C760-C768, C809), no further checking is done.\r\n3.  If Sequence Number--Hospital is in the range of 60-88, this edit is skipped.\r\n\r\nIt is important to verify that the non-microscopically confirmed case is indeed a separate primary from any others that may have been reported. This edit forces review of multiple primary cancers when one of the primaries is coded to a site other than ill-defined or unknown and is not microscopically confirmed or confirmed by a positive lab test/marker study.\r\n\r\n1.  If the suspect case is confirmed accurate as coded and if the number of primaries is correct, set the Over-ride HospSeq/DxConf to 1. Do not set the over-ride flag on the patient''s other primary cancers.\r\n2.  If it turns out that the non-microscopically confirmed cancer is considered a manifestation of one of the patient''s other cancers, delete the non-microscopically confirmed case. Check the sequence numbers of remaining cases, correcting them if necessary. Also check for other data items on the remaining cases that may need to be changed as a result of the corrections, such as stage and treatment.\r\n\r\n**Instructions for Coding**\r\n\r\n*   Leave blank if the program does not generate an error message for the edit Diagnostic Confirm, Seq Num--Hosp (CoC).\r\n*   Leave blank and correct any errors for the case if an item is discovered to be incorrect.\r\n*   Code 1 if review of all items in the error or warning message confirms that all are correct.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "No recommendation",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "alternate_names": [
      "Over-ride Hospital Sequence/Diagnostic Confirmation"
    ],
    "allowable_values": "1 or blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed as reported"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not reviewed or reviewed and corrected"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1988",
    "item_name": "Over-ride HospSeq/Site",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2001",
    "version_implemented": "9",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "overRideHospseqSite",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2011-11-10T05:47:21Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-09-15T09:15:46.455849Z",
    "description": "Some computer edits identify errors. Others indicate possible errors that require manual review for resolution. To eliminate the need to review the same cases repeatedly, over-ride flags have been developed to indicate that data in a record (or records) have been reviewed and, while unusual, are correct.\r\n\r\nThis over-ride is used with the following edits in the NAACCR Metafile of the EDITS software:\r\n\r\n*   Seq Num--Hosp, Primary Site, Morph ICDO2 (CoC)\r\n*   Seq Num--Hosp, Primary Site, Morph ICDO3 (CoC)",
    "rationale": "Some edits check for code combinations that are possible, but quite rare. If the code combination generates an error message and review of the case indicates that the codes are correct for the case, then the over-ride flag is used to skip the edit in the future. See [**Standards for Cancer Registries, Standard Data Edits**](https://www.naaccr.org/standard-data-edits/).\r\n\r\n**Over-ride Flag as Used in the EDITS Software Package**\r\n\r\nEdits of the type Seq Num--Hosp, Primary Site, Morph differ in use of ICD-O-2 or ICD-O-3 morphology. They force review of multiple primary cancers when one of the primaries is coded to a site/morphology combination that could indicate a metastatic site rather than a primary site.\r\n\r\n1.    If Sequence Number--Hospital indicates the person has had more than one primary, then any case with one of the following site/histology combinations requires review:\r\n    *   C760-C768 (ill-defined sites) or C809 (unknown primary) and ICD-O-2 or ICD-O-3 histology less than 9590. Look for evidence that the unknown or ill-defined primary is a secondary site from one of the patient''s other cancers. For example, a clinical discharge diagnosis of \"abdominal carcinomatosis\" may be attributable to the patient’s primary ovarian cystadenocarcinoma already in the registry, and should not be entered as a second primary.\r\n    *   C770-C779 (lymph nodes) and ICD-O-2 histology not in range 9590-9717 or ICD-O-3 histology not in the range 9590-9729; or C420-C424 and ICD-O-2 histology not in range 9590-9941 or ICD-O-3 histology not in the range 9590-9989. That combination is most likely a metastatic lesion. Check whether the lesion could be a manifestation of one of the patient’s other cancers.\r\n    *   Any site and ICD-O-2 histology in the range 9720-9723, 9740-9741 or ICD-O-3 histology in the range 9740-9758. Verify that these diagnoses are coded correctly and are indeed separate primaries from the others\r\n2.    If it turns out that the suspect tumor is a manifestation of one of the patient''s other cancers, delete the metastatic or secondary case, re-sequence remaining cases, and correct the coding on the original case as necessary.\r\n\r\n**Instructions for Coding**\r\n\r\n*   Leave blank if the program does not generate an error message for an edit of the type Seq Num--Hosp, Primary Site, Morph.\r\n*   Leave blank and correct any errors for the case if an item is discovered to be incorrect.\r\n*   Code 1 if review of all items in the error or warning message confirms that hospital sequence number and site are both correct.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "No recommendation",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "alternate_names": [
      "Over-ride Hospital Sequence/Site"
    ],
    "allowable_values": "1 or blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed as reported"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not reviewed or reviewed and corrected"
      }
    ]
  },
