    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2017-11-14T16:13:44Z",
    "date_modified": "2022-05-27T07:24:12Z",
    "description": "Some computer edits identify errors. Others indicate possible errors that require manual review for resolution. To eliminate the need to review the same cases repeatedly, over-ride flags have been developed to indicate that data in a record (or records) have been reviewed and, while unusual, are correct.",
    "rationale": "Some edits check for code combinations that are possible, but quite rare. If the code combination generates an error message and review of the case indicates that the codes are correct for the case, then the over-ride flag is used to skip the edit in the future.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "No recommendation",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "allowable_values": "1, Blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed as reported"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not reviewed or reviewed and corrected"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1992",
    "item_name": "Over-ride TNM Stage",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2018",
    "version_implemented": "18",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "overRideTnmStage",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2017-11-14T16:11:51Z",
    "date_modified": "2022-05-27T07:24:12Z",
    "description": "Some computer edits identify errors. Others indicate possible errors that require manual review for resolution. To eliminate the need to review the same cases repeatedly, over-ride flags have been developed to indicate that data in a record (or records) have been reviewed and, while unusual, are correct.  \n  \n  \nThis over-ride is used with the following edits in the NAACCR Metafile of the EDITS software:  \n  \n* Primary Site, TNM Clin Stage Valid A- Ed 7 (CoC)\n* Primary Site, TNM Clin Stage Valid B- Ed 7 (CoC)\n* Primary Site, TNM Path Stage Valid A- Ed 7 (CoC)\n* Primary Site, TNM Path Stage Valid B- Ed 7 (CoC)\n\nThese edits check T, N, and M combinations against stage group. Adding this over-ride allows the edit to pass when combinations of T, N, and M are entered that are not included in the stage tables used with the edits.   \n ",
    "rationale": "This over-ride will allow registrars to enter combination of T, N, and M with a stage group that differs from the combinations documented in the AJCC Staging Manual.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "No recommendation",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "allowable_values": "1, Blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed as reported"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not reviewed or reviewed and corrected"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1993",
    "item_name": "Over-ride TNM Tis",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2018",
    "version_implemented": "18",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "overRideTnmTis",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Edit Overrides/Conversion History/System Admin",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2017-11-14T16:12:50Z",
    "date_modified": "2022-05-27T07:24:09Z",
    "description": "Some computer edits identify errors. Others indicate possible errors that require manual review for resolution. To eliminate the need to review the same cases repeatedly, over-ride flags have been developed to indicate that data in a record (or records) have been reviewed and, while unusual, are correct.  \n  \n  \nThis over-ride is used with the following edits in the NAACCR Metafile of the EDITS software:  \n  \n* TNM Clin T, N, M, In Situ (CoC)\n* TNM Path T, N, M, In Situ (CoC)\n\nIf the patient has a T value indicating in situ/ noninvasive, this edit verifies that the N, M, and stage group reflect in situ/noninvasive disease. However, there are certain circumstances where AJCC does allow a T value indicating in situ/noninvasive and N, M, and/or stage group that indicates invasive disease. An over-ride is required to accommodate these situations.  \n ",
    "rationale": "This over-ride will allow registrars to enter combination of T, N, and M with a stage group that differs from the combinations documented in the AJCC Staging Manual.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Required",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "allowable_values": "1, Blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Reviewed and confirmed as reported"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not reviewed or reviewed and corrected"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "3956",
    "item_name": "p16",
    "item_data_type": "text",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2022",
    "version_implemented": "22",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "p16",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Stage/Prognostic Factors",
    "source_of_standard": "SEER",
    "date_created": "2021-06-04T10:06:30Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-07-08T13:37:32.86628Z",
    "description": "The p16 biomarker is over-expressed (produced) in response to HPV. It is therefore a surrogate marker for HPV disease.",
    "general_notes": "p16 is a tumor suppressor protein also known as cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitor 2A. The p16 biomarker is over-expressed (produced) in response to HPV. It is therefore a surrogate marker for HPV disease.",
    "rationale": "Patients with HPV have a different survival or outcome so it is important to be able to distinguish this by documenting the p16 results. Testing is performed by immunohistochemistry (IHC) which is inexpensive and has near universal availability. It has an easily standardized interpretation. HPV testing is usually performed through DNA testing which is more expensive and less widely available. HPV testing also has technically more variability with the interpretation.",
    "npcr_collect": "Required, site specific",
    "coc_collect": "Required, site specific",
    "seer_collect": "Required, site specific",
    "cccr_collect": "Required, site specific; when available",
    "code_note": "Note: See the [SSDI Manual](https://apps.naaccr.org/ssdi/list/?_gl=1*111s1ff*_ga*NTAyNDk1MDUwLjE1OTI5Mzk3MDY.*_ga_ZGX07SVHJF*MTY1NDU0NDUzMy40LjEuMTY1NDU0NDcwNi4w&_ga=2.89925727.598791132.1654524231-502495050.1592939706) for coding instructions.  \r\nAnus schema added/ Please note for CCCR p16 for Cervix changed from \".\" to RS\\* retroactive to 2021",
    "allowable_values": "0, 1, 8, 9, blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "0",
        "description": "p16 Negative; Nonreactive"
      },
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "p16 Positive; Diffuse, Strong reactivity"
      },
      {
        "code": "8",
        "description": "Not applicable: Information not collected for this case  \n (If this time is required by your standard setter, use of code 8 will result in an edit error)."
      },
      {
        "code": "9",
        "description": "Not tested for p16; Unknown"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Diagnosis year prior to 2024"
      }
    ]
  },
