    "description": "Pediatric Primary Tumor is part of the Pediatric Staging data collection system and is used to classify contiguous growth (extension) of the primary tumor within the organ of origin or its direct extension into neighboring organs. See also Pediatric Regional Nodes \\[1137\\], and Pediatric Mets \\[1138\\]. Effective for cases diagnosed 1/1/2024 and forward.",
    "rationale": "Pediatric Primary Tumor is used to calculate Derived Pediatric T \\[1142\\] (when applicable). Derivation will occur at the level of the central registry.",
