    "date_modified": "2022-05-27T07:24:12Z",
    "description": "Pleural effusion is the accumulation of fluid between the parietal pleura (the pleura covering the chest wall and diaphragm) and the visceral pleura (the pleura covering the lungs).",
    "rationale": "Pleural Effusion is collected by the surveillance community for pleura cancers. Prior to 2018, Pleura SSF #1 was used for Pleural Effusion.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "Required, site specific",
    "seer_collect": "Required, site specific",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "code_note": "Each Site-Specific Data Item (SSDI) applies only to selected primary sites, histologies, and years of diagnosis. Depending on applicability and standard-setter requirements, SSDIs may be left blank.",
    "allowable_values": "0-4, 8, 9",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "0",
        "description": "Pleural effusion not identified/not present"
      },
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Pleural effusion present, non-malignant (negative)"
      },
      {
        "code": "2",
        "description": "Pleural effusion present, malignant (positive)  \n Physician states pleural effusion is malignant in the absence of positive cytology"
      },
      {
        "code": "3",
        "description": "Pleural effusion, atypical/atypical mesothelial cells"
      },
      {
        "code": "4",
        "description": "Pleural effusion, NOS"
      },
      {
        "code": "8",
        "description": "Not applicable: Information not collected for this case  \n (If this item is required by your standard setter, use of code 8 will result in an edit error.)"
      },
      {
        "code": "9",
        "description": "Not documented in medical record  \n Pleural Effusion not assessed or unknown if assessed"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1192",
    "item_name": "Pretext Clinical Staging",
    "item_data_type": "numeric",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2025",
    "version_implemented": "25",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "pretextClinicalStaging",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Stage/Prognostic Factors",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR/SEER",
    "date_created": "2024-04-26T09:50:10.734083Z",
    "date_modified": "2024-05-30T20:57:26.844109Z",
    "description": "PRETEXT stands for PRE-Treatment Extent of tumor. This field describes the extent of involvement within the four lobes of the liver at time of a pediatric liver tumor diagnosis. It is based off clinical imaging and was originally designed to standardize imaging evaluation and risk stratification of hepatoblastoma before neoadjuvant chemotherapy or tumor resection.",
    "general_notes": "**Source documents:** imaging",
    "rationale": "After initially being created by the International Childhood Liver Tumours Strategy Group (SIOPEL) in 1990, PRETEXT was introduced for use within the United States in 2014 by the Children’s Oncology Group (COG) once radiographic imaging became more sophisticated and exploratory surgery at diagnosis was no longer advisable. It is used as a central component of risk stratification schemes that define treatment of hepatoblastoma.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Required, site specific; when available",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "code_note": "**Note 1: Effective years**\r\n\r\n*   This SSDI is effective for diagnosis years 2024+\r\n*   For cases diagnosed 2018-2023, this SSDI must be blank\r\n\r\n**Note 2: Criteria for coding**\r\n\r\n*   This SSDI is based on imaging findings only\\*\\*. Do not\\*\\* code any findings from surgical resection in this data item. Evaluation must also be done prior to any neoadjuvant therapy\r\n\r\n**Note 3: Pretext Staging-Segments of the live**r\r\n\r\n*   Caudate liver: Segment I  \r\n    _**Note**_: Involvement of the caudate liver is at minimum Stage 2\r\n*   Left lateral section: Segments II & III\r\n*   Left medial section: Segments IVA & IVB\r\n*   Right anterior section: Segments V & VIII\r\n*   Right posterior section: Segments VI & VII",
    "allowable_values": "1-4, 8, 9",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "One section involved; three adjoining sections are tumor free\r\n\r\nStage I, Pretext 1"
      },
      {
        "code": "2",
        "description": "One or two sections involved; two adjoining sections are tumor free\r\n\r\nStage 2, Pretext 2"
      },
      {
        "code": "3",
        "description": "Two or three sections involved; one adjoining section is tumor free\r\n\r\nStage 3, Pretext 3"
      },
      {
        "code": "4",
        "description": "Four sections involved\r\n\r\nStage 4, Pretext 4"
      },
      {
        "code": "8",
        "description": "Not applicable: Information not collected for this case  \r\n(If this information is required by your standard setter, use of code 8 may result in an edit error.)"
      },
      {
        "code": "9",
        "description": "Not documented in medical record\r\n\r\nCannot be determined by pathologist\r\n\r\nPRETEXT not assessed or unknown if assessed"
      }
    ]
  },
