    ],
    "section": "Text-Treatment",
    "source_of_standard": "NPCR",
    "date_created": "2011-11-09T14:47:21Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-05-10T12:45:48.333398Z",
    "description": "Text area for information describing all surgical procedures performed as part of treatment.",
    "general_notes": "**Data Item(s) to be verified/validated using the text entered in this field** After manual entry of the text field, ensure that the text entered both agrees with the coded values and clearly justifies the selected codes in the following fields:\r\n\r\n| **Item name** | **Item number** |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| Date Initial RX SEER | 1260 |\r\n| Date 1st Crs RX CoC | 1270 |\r\n| RX Date Surgery | 1200 |\r\n| RX Summ--Surg Prim Site | 1290 |\r\n| RX Hosp--Surg Prim Site | 670 |\r\n| RX Summ--Scope Reg LN Sur | 1292 |\r\n| RX Hosp--Scope Reg LN Sur | 672 |\r\n| RX Summ--Surg Oth Reg/Dis | 1294 |\r\n| RX Hosp--Surg Oth Reg/Dis | 674 |\r\n| Reason for No Surgery | 1340 |\r\n| RX Summ--Surgical Margins | 1320 |\r\n| RX Hosp--Palliative Proc | 3280 |\r\n| RX Summ--Palliative Proc | 3270 |\r\n| Text--Place of Diagnosis | 2690 |\r\n| RX Summ--Surg/Rad Seq | 1380 |\r\n| RX Summ--Systemic/Sur Seq | 1639 |",
    "rationale": "Text documentation is an essential component of a complete electronic report and is heavily utilized for quality control and special studies. Text is needed to justify coded values and to document supplemental information not transmitted within coded values. High-quality text documentation facilitates consolidation of information from multiple reporting sources at the central registry.\r\n\r\nThe text field must contain a description that has been entered by the reporter independently from the code(s). If software generates text automatically from codes, the text cannot be utilized to check coded values. Information documenting the disease process should be entered manually from the medical record **and should not be generated electronically from coded values**. \r\n\r\n**Instructions**\r\n\r\n*   Prioritize entered information in the order of the fields listed below.\r\n*   Text automatically generated from coded data is not acceptable.\r\n*   NAACCR-approved abbreviations should be utilized (see Appendix G).\r\n*   Do not repeat information from other text fields.\r\n*   Additional comments can be continued in empty text fields, including Remarks. For text documentation that is continued from one text field to another, use asterisks or other symbols to indicate the connection with preceding text.\r\n*   If information is missing from the record, state that it is missing.\r\n*   Do not include irrelevant information.\r\n*   Do not include information that the registry is not authorized to collect.\r\n\r\n_Note:_ For software that allows unlimited text, NAACCR recommends that the software indicate to the reporter the portion of the text that will be transmitted to the central registry. \r\n\r\n**Suggestions for text:**\r\n\r\n*   Date of each procedure.\r\n*   Type(s) of surgical procedure(s), including excisional biopsies and surgery to other and distant sites.\r\n*   Lymph nodes removed.\r\n*   Regional tissues removed.\r\n*   Metastatic sites.\r\n*   Facility where each procedure was performed.\r\n*   Record positive and negative findings. Record positive findings first.\r\n*   Other treatment information, e.g., planned procedure aborted; unknown if surgery performed.",
    "npcr_collect": "Required, these text requirements may be met with one or several text block fields",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Required",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "format": "Free text",
    "allowable_values": "Neither carriage return nor line feed characters allowed"
  },
  {
    "item_number": "3923",
    "item_name": "S Category Clinical",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2018",
    "version_implemented": "18",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "sCategoryClinical",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Stage/Prognostic Factors",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2017-11-14T06:36:27Z",
    "date_modified": "2022-05-27T07:24:13Z",
    "description": "S Category Clinical combines the results of pre-orchiectomy Alpha Fetoprotein (AFP), Human Chorionic Gonadotropin (hCG) and Lactate Dehydrogenase (LDH) into a summary S value.",
    "rationale": "S Category Clinical is required for prognostic stage grouping in AJCC 8th edition, Chapter 59 *Testis*. It is a new data item for cases diagnosed 1/1/2018+.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "Required, site specific",
    "seer_collect": "Required, site specific",
    "cccr_collect": "Required, site specific; when available",
    "code_note": "\\*N indicates the upper limit of normal for the LDH assay.   \n   \nEach Site-Specific Data Item (SSDI) applies only to selected primary sites, histologies, and years of diagnosis. Depending on applicability and standard-setter requirements, SSDIs may be left blank. ",
    "allowable_values": "0-3, 9",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "0",
        "description": "S0: Marker study levels within normal levels"
      },
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "S1: At least one of these values is elevated AND  \n LDH less than 1.5 x N\\* AND  \n hCG (mIU/L) less than 5,000 AND  \n AFP (ng/mL) less than 1,000"
      },
      {
        "code": "2",
        "description": "S2:  \n LDH 1.5 x N\\* to 10 x N\\* OR  \n hCG (mIU/L) 5,000 to 50,000 OR  \n AFP (ng/mL) 1,000 to 10,000"
      },
      {
        "code": "3",
        "description": "S3: Only one elevated test is needed  \n LDH greater than 10 x N\\* OR  \n hcG (mIU/mL) greater than 50,000 OR  \n AFP (ng/mL) greater than 10,000"
      },
      {
        "code": "9",
        "description": "SX: Not documented in medical record  \n S Category Clinical not assessed or unknown if assessed"
      }
    ]
  },
