    "seer_collect": "Derived",
    "cccr_collect": "Required, when available",
    "code_note": "Schema ID Version Original is a code with up to 2 digits, a decimal and then up to 2 more digits. (e.g., 1.5, 10.12). The first two digits represent the major version number related to diagnosis year; the second two digits represent minor version changes with the diagnosis years. Minimum allowable value would be “1.0”. Maximum allowable value would be “99.99”.  Blanks would not be allowed.  \r\n   \r\nThis data item will be generated by registry software. No coding instructions are required.",
