    "description": "Serum Beta-2 Microglobulin is a protein that is found on the surface of many cells and plentiful on the surface of white blood cells. Increased production or destruction of these cells causes Serum β2 (beta-2) Microglobulin level to increase. Elevated Serum β2 (beta-2) Microglobulin level is a prognostic factor for plasma cell myeloma.",
    "rationale": "Serum Beta-2 Microglobulin Pretreatment Level is a prognostic factor required in AJCC 8th edition, Chapter 82 _Plasma Cell Myeloma and Plasma Cell Disorders_, for staging of plasma cell myeloma.",
