    "description": "The Surv-Date Active Followup is defined as the earlier of the Date of Last Contact \\[1750\\] and a study cutoff date. The study cut-off date is a pre-determined date based on the year of data submission and is set in the survival program used to derive the seven survival variables. If the Date of Last Contact \\[1750\\] is earlier than the study cut-off date and either the day or month is unknown or not available, the values are imputed by the survival program. The survival program is available from your standard setter or NAACCR.\r\n\r\n**Example 1**\r\n\r\nDate of Last Contact: 20111120\r\n\r\nStudy Cut-off Date: 20111231\r\n\r\nSurv-Date Active Followup: 20111120\r\n\r\nNote: The date of last contact is earlier than the study cut-off date, and the date of last contact is complete, so the date of last contact is used in Surv-Date Active Followup.\r\n\r\n**Example 2**\r\n\r\nDate of Last Contact: 201111\r\n\r\nStudy Cut-off Date: 20111231\r\n\r\nSurv-Date Active Followup: 20111115\r\n\r\nNote: Rationale is to take mid-point of possible values. For Nov (30 days) it would be FLOOR((1+30)/2) = 15, where FLOOR is a function that rounds a decimal down to an integer.",
    "general_notes": "Additional information about the survival algorithm and what specific values are assigned in given missing date situations are available here: \\<http://seer.cancer.gov/survivaltime/\\>.",
    "rationale": "The Surv-Date Active Followup is needed to be able to recalculate survival months if a different study cut-off date is used and provides flexibility to recalculate survival without needing to rerun the survival program on the original data.",
    "npcr_collect": "Derived",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Derived",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "format": "YYYYMMDD",
    "code_note": "If Date of Last Contact \\[1750\\] is blank, Surv-Date Active Followup will also be blank.",
    "allowable_values": "Valid Dates"
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1788",
    "item_name": "Surv-Date DX Recode",
    "item_data_type": "date",
    "item_length": "8",
    "year_implemented": "2015",
    "version_implemented": "15",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "survDateDxRecode",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Follow-up/Recurrence/Death",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2014-08-13T11:37:40Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-05-10T17:49:07.202063Z",
    "description": "The survival date of diagnosis recode is calculated using the month, day, and year of the Date of Diagnosis \\[390\\]. If the Date of Diagnosis \\[390\\] has complete month and day information, the Surv-Date Dx Recode will be the same as the Date of Diagnosis \\[390\\]. If the day or month is unknown or not available, the values are imputed by the survival program used to derive the seven survival variables. The survival program is available from your standard setter or NAACCR.\r\n\r\n**Example 1**\r\n\r\nDate of diagnosis: 20111199\r\n\r\nDate of Last Contact: 20111120\r\n\r\nSurv-Date of DX Recode: 20111110\r\n\r\nNote: The recoded value is the mid-point between 11/1 and 11/20.\r\n\r\n**Example 2**\r\n\r\nDate of diagnosis: 2011\r\n\r\nDate of Last Contact: 20111120\r\n\r\nSurv-Date of DX Recode: 20110611\r\n\r\nNote: The recoded value is the mid-point between 20110101 and 20111120.",
    "general_notes": "Additional information about the survival algorithm and what specific values are assigned in given missing date situations are available here: [http://seer.cancer.gov/survivaltime/](http://seer.cancer.gov/survivaltime/).",
    "rationale": "The Surv-Date DX Recode is needed to be able to match to a lifetable entry to obtain expected survival. If a case is diagnosed in January 2000, the first 12 months of expected survival will be from the 2000 life table. If a case is diagnosed in December 2000, only one month will be from the 2000 life table and then the 2001 life table is used.",
    "npcr_collect": "Derived",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Derived",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "format": "YYYYMMDD",
    "allowable_values": "Valid dates"
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1785",
    "item_name": "Surv-Date Presumed Alive",
    "item_data_type": "date",
    "item_length": "8",
    "year_implemented": "2015",
    "version_implemented": "15",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "survDatePresumedAlive",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Follow-up/Recurrence/Death",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2014-08-20T12:23:51Z",
    "date_modified": "2023-05-10T17:50:12.785233Z",
    "description": "The Surv-Date Presumed Alive is the last date for which complete death ascertainment is available from the registry at the time a file is transmitted. Because not all central cancer registries conduct active patient follow-up, it is necessary to have an option for calculating survival times based on the assumption that the registry has ascertained all available deaths (state/province and national), and persons not known to be deceased are presumed to be alive as of the last date for which complete death ascertainment is available. This variable is set in the survival program used to derive the seven survival variables. The survival program is available from your standard setter or NAACCR.\r\n\r\n**Example 1**\r\n\r\nVital Status: Alive\r\n\r\nDate of Last Contact: 20111120\r\n\r\nStudy Cut-off Date: 20111231\r\n\r\nLatest date for complete death ascertainment: 20111231\r\n\r\nSurv-Date Presumed Alive: 20111231",
    "general_notes": "Additional information about the survival algorithm and what specific values are assigned in given missing date situations are available here: [http://seer.cancer.gov/survivaltime/](http://seer.cancer.gov/survivaltime/).",
    "rationale": "The Surv-Date Presumed Alive is needed to be able to recalculate survival months if a different study cut-off date is used and provides flexibility to recalculate survival without needing to rerun the survival program on the original data.",
    "npcr_collect": "Derived",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Derived",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "format": "YYYYMMDD",
    "allowable_values": "Valid dates"
  },
  {
    "item_number": "1783",
    "item_name": "Surv-Flag Active Followup",
    "item_data_type": "digits",
    "item_length": "1",
    "year_implemented": "2015",
    "version_implemented": "15",
    "xml_naaccr_id": "survFlagActiveFollowup",
    "xml_parent_id": "Tumor",
    "record_types": [
      "A",
      "C",
      "I",
      "M"
    ],
    "section": "Follow-up/Recurrence/Death",
    "source_of_standard": "NAACCR",
    "date_created": "2014-08-20T01:44:16Z",
    "date_modified": "2022-05-27T07:24:10Z",
    "description": "This flag is generated by the program that creates Surv-Mos Active Followup [1784] and describes how complete the date information is that was used to calculate survival months. This item is one of seven survival variables designed to facilitate a common approach to survival analysis by NAACCR registries.",
    "rationale": "The flag will enable analysts to easily select a subset of cases.",
    "npcr_collect": "Derived",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Derived",
    "cccr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "allowable_values": "0-3, 8,9, blank",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "0",
        "description": "Complete dates are available and there are 0 days of survival (i.e., date last contact = date of diagnosis)"
      },
      {
        "code": "1",
        "description": "Complete dates are available and there are more than 0 days of survival (i.e., date last contact > date diagnosis)"
      },
      {
        "code": "2",
        "description": "Incomplete dates are available and there could be zero days of follow-up (i.e., known components are equal, e.g., 2006 and 20061002)"
      },
      {
        "code": "3",
        "description": "Incomplete dates are available and there cannot be zero days of follow-up (i.e., any difference in known date components, e.g., 200602 and 200603)"
      },
      {
        "code": "8",
        "description": "Not calculated because a Death Certificate Only or Autopsy Only case"
      },
      {
        "code": "9",
        "description": "Unknown"
      },
      {
        "code": "Blank",
        "description": "Not coded"
      }
    ]
  },
