    "description": "This data item records the size of a solid primary tumor **before any treatment** (surgical resection or initiation of any treatment including neoadjuvant).",
    "rationale": "Clinical tumor size (pre-treatment size) is essential for treatment decision making and prognosis determination for many types of cancer.",
    "npcr_collect": "No recommendation",
    "coc_collect": "No recommendation",
    "seer_collect": "Historically collected and currently transmitted",
    "cccr_collect": "Required, when available",
    "code_description": "Refer to the most recent version of** [**SEER Program Coding and Staging Manual**](http://seer.cancer.gov/tools/codingmanuals/) **for additional instructions.",
    "allowable_values": "000-990, 998, 999",
    "allowed_codes": [
      {
        "code": "000",
        "description": "No mass/tumor found"
      },
      {
        "code": "001",
        "description": "1 mm or described as **less than** 1 mm (0.1 cm or less than 0.1 cm)"
      },
      {
        "code": "002-988",
        "description": "Exact size in millimeters (2 mm to 988 mm) (0.2 to 98.8 cm)"
      },
      {
        "code": "989",
        "description": "989 millimeters or larger (98.9 cm or larger)"
      },
      {
        "code": "990",
        "description": "Microscopic focus or foci only and no size of focus is given"
      },
      {
        "code": "998",
        "description": "SITE-SPECIFIC CODES  \n   \n Alternate descriptions of tumor size for specific sites:  \n   \n Familial/multiple polyposis:  \n -Rectosigmoid and rectum (C19.9, C20.9)  \n -Colon (C18.0, C18.2-C18.9)  \n   \n **If no size is documented:**  \n Circumferential:  \n -Esophagus (C15.0-C15.5, C15.8, C15.9)  \n   \n Diffuse; widespread: 3/4s or more; linitis plastica:  \n -Stomach and Esophagus GE Junction (C16.0-C16.6, C16.8, C16.9)  \n   \n Diffuse, entire lung or NOS:  \n -Lung and main stem bronchus (C34.0-C34.3, C34.8, C34.9)  \n   \n Diffuse:  \n -Breast (C50.0-C50.6, C50.8, C50.9)"
      },
      {
        "code": "999",
        "description": "Unknown; size not stated; Not documented in patient record; Size of tumor cannot be assessed; The only measurement(s) describes pieces or chips; Not applicable"
      }
    ]
  },
